public class Obj
extends Parametric
implements iTransformable

Objects

Object is a combination of faces, points and lines. In OOG, while the primary focus is a logic representation, the Object doesn't have limitations such as BREP data structures of volumetric information. An object could be composed of a point (1D) or line (2D).

orphaned

public Obj orphaned()
Export the geometry without any Parametric features. The geometry becomes static and loose all dynamic relationships between objects. Become all Pt derived or linked to antoher becomes x y z, Faces and Pts are set of static points.

toEnergyPlus

public void toEnergyPlus(TextIO out)
Text formated as energyPlus code. Export every faces with zone name each Obj corresponds to a zone in EnergyPlus it must have a name and subsequent surfaces must refer to that name 
 
 Zone,
 NORTH_ZONE,              !- Name
 0,                       !- Direction of Relative North {deg}
 0,                       !- X Origin {m}
 0,                       !- Y Origin {m}
 0,                       !- Z Origin {m}
 1,                       !- Type
 1,                       !- Multiplier
 autocalculate;           !- Ceiling Height {m}

 TODO check if lines or points needed for further control

Parameters:
zoneDown - - zone name
out - - PrintWriter in file

toModelicaBuildings

public void toModelicaBuildings(TextIO out)
Text formated as Modelica code using Buildings library. Export every faces with zone name Meant to be linked with EnergyPlus as airflow network extension. Thus each Obj corresponds to a volume in Buildings it must have a name and subsequent surfaces must refer to that name 
 
  Buildings.Fluid.MixingVolumes.MixingVolume volEas(
    redeclare package Medium = Medium,
    T_start=273.15 + 20,
    V=2.5*5*5*1,
    nPorts=6,
    use_HeatTransfer=true,
    energyDynamics=Modelica.Fluid.Types.Dynamics.DynamicFreeInitial,
    massDynamics=Modelica.Fluid.Types.Dynamics.DynamicFreeInitial,
    traceDynamics=Modelica.Fluid.Types.Dynamics.FixedInitial,
    C_nominal={1E-6})     ;

Buildings.Fluid.Sources.PrescribedExtraPropertyFlowRate sou(redeclare package
      Medium =  Medium, use_m_flow_in=true,
    nPorts=1) "CO2 source"

Buildings.Fluid.Sensors.TraceSubstances senCO2(redeclare package
      Medium = Medium) "CO2 Sensor"


Modelica.Blocks.Math.Gain gaiCO2(k=8.18E-6) "CO2 emission per person"

Parameters:
zoneDown - - zone name
out - - PrintWriter in file
